            .</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by Mr. Knapp. Q. You do not know whether there may not be a recent account opened in that name? - A. I know that there is not.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17981205-24-person419">
                  Q. 
               <interp inst="t17981205-24-person419" type="given" value="Q."></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17981205-24-person419" type="gender" value="indeterminate"></interp>
                  </persName>
            You are not certain of the check, nor the person? - A. No.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17981205-24-person420">
                  Q. 
               <interp inst="t17981205-24-person420" type="given" value="Q."></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17981205-24-person420" type="gender" value="indeterminate"></interp>
                  </persName>
            (To John Patrick.) Look at that check again, and tell me whether you recollect the gentleman that stands by you? - A. Yes, I do, perfectly well.</p>
               <p>Q. Mr. Beesley was in the shop at the time? - A. Yes.</p>
               <p>Q. You are sure you presented the check to him? - A. Yes, I am; I then carried it home, and gave it to my father.</p>
               <p>Mr. Knapp. (To Beesley.) Q. The knowledge you have, of who has an account opened or not, is from your books? - A. Yes.</p>
               <p>Q. It must be a reference to a book which furnishes you with the knowledge whether there is or not an account opened? - A. Yes.</p>
               <p>Q. That book is not here? - A. No.</p>
               <p>Court. Q. Does your house keep accounts but in a book? - A. Certainly not.</p>
               <p>Court. Q. Have you looked carefully over your books? - A. I have; I can venture safely to swear there is no such account in the books.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17981205-24-person421">
                  GEORGE
                   LONGDEN
               <interp inst="t17981205-24-person421" type="surname" value="LONGDEN"></interp>
